---
## Context
{{ context | default("What is this issue about? Why is it needed now? Reference concept nodes with [[node-id]] so the validator can check them.") }}

## Implements
{{ implements_text | default("Which requirements, decisions, or contracts does this implement? Use [[reference]] if they exist as nodes.") }}

## Repo scope
- Repo: {{ repo | default("<org>/<repo>") }}
- Base branch: {{ base_branch | default("test") }}
- Primary paths: {{ primary_paths | default("<list of files or directories this will touch>") }}
- Required config: {{ required_config | default("<[[config-node]] references or env var names>") }}

## Requirements
{{ requirements | default("Bullet list of requirements. Be specific — agents read this literally.") }}

## Execution constraints
- Do not make new product or architecture decisions.
- If any ambiguity blocks correct work, stop and ask in the issue comments (or via a blocking message for containerised agents).

## Acceptance criteria
- [ ] {{ criterion_1 | default("First acceptance criterion") }}
- [ ] {{ criterion_2 | default("Second acceptance criterion") }}
- [ ] CI passing
- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified by the verifier

## Test plan
```bash
{{ test_commands | default("# Commands to run to verify this issue\nuv run pytest tests/unit/test_<module>.py -v\nmake lint") }}
```

## Dependencies
{{ dependencies | default("List any blocking issues by key, or write `none` if standalone. Also reference `[[concept-nodes]]` this work depends on.") }}

## Definition of Done
- [ ] Implementation complete
- [ ] Tests added/updated
- [ ] Completion comment added
- [ ] docs/issues/{{ id | default("<KEY>") }}/developer.md added
- [ ] docs/issues/{{ id | default("<KEY>") }}/verified.md added
- [ ] Concept nodes created/updated for new artifacts
